
    Facts are the values that are inferred
    from the remote system's current state or
    nature.

    Facts are used to determine if a change
    needs to be made or not.

Module
    Modules are the things that perform some
    action on the remote system.

    They can be simple or complex, and can
    be written in any language.

    Ansible modules are written in Python, and
    can be written in any other language by using
    a :term:`Connection Plugin`.

    Modules can be executed synchronously or
    asynchronously.

    When a module is executed synchronously, Ansible
    will wait for the task to complete before moving
    on to the next task in a play.

    When a module is executed asynchronously, Ansible
    will queue up the task and continue on to the next
    task in a play without waiting for
